x4freetext: Corrected for background.
Error of the absolute cross sections.
Enriched 24Mg metal (>=99%), rolled to thin self-
supporting foils with thickness of 65 microg/cm2.
Two large NaI(Tl) crystals.
Both gamma detectors at 90 degrees to the incoming
beam. Distance from target to detector face varied
between 15 and 17.5 cm.
For gamma 0, angular distribution assumed to
be sin2(theta) dependent; an isotropic angular
distribution was assumed for gamma 1.
Slight correction included for solid angle of the
detector.
